1.- Open a Terminal (Applications-Accesories-Terminal) and type:

sudo apt-get install conky-all lm-sensors hddtemp


2. Press CTRL H  and see the hidden files

3.  Go to .Conky/sentinel/font/ and install all truetype fonts.

4. put all the .conkyrc files & .start-conky file into home.

5.- Now, just copy .Conky folder to home folder

6. Go to System-Preferences-Start_Applications. Add. In dialog Box (Command) just write: /home/use your user name/.start-conky. Or better yet find the .start-conky and double click and check the box to start-up.

Reboot. Now, Conky Sentinel is running!
